  .courseblock-span4.heading
    %h3 Scratch Jr.
    %h4 
      Grades K-2
      %br
      Platform: iPad & Android
      %br
      Price: Free
    .smalltext Scratch Jr. is an introductory programming language that enables young children (ages 5-7) to create their own interactive stories and games. Children snap together graphical programming blocks to make characters move, jump, dance, and sing. Children can modify characters in the paint editor, add their own voices and sounds, even insert photos of themselves - then use the programming blocks to make their characters come to life.
    %br
    %a{:href=>"http://www.scratchjr.org/teach.html#curricula"}
      %button{:style=>'margin-left:10px'} Download Scratch Jr. Curriculum
    %a{:href=>"http://www.scratchjr.org/"}
      %button{:style=>'margin-top: 10px; margin-left:10px'} Visit Scratch Jr.

